LOOPS-
loops is used when same code needs to run multiple times based on condition 

for - 
import java.util.*;
public class practice1 {
    public static void main(String[] args) {
        Scanner sc = new Scanner(System.in);
        System.out.println("enter number");
        int num= sc.nextInt();
        for(int i=0;i<=num;i++){
         System.out.println(i);
      }
    }
}

while -
import java.util.*;
public class practice1 {
    public static void main(String[] args) {
        Scanner sc = new Scanner(System.in);
        System.out.println("enter number");
        int num= sc.nextInt();
        int i=0;
        while ( i<=num ) {
        System.out.println(i);
        i++;
      }
    }
}

do while -
import java.util.*;
public class practice1 {
  public static void main(String[] args) {
    Scanner sc = new Scanner(System.in);
    System.out.println("enter number");
    int num = sc.nextInt();
    int i = 0;
    do {
      System.out.println(i);
      i++;
    } while (i < 5);
  }
}

Task1- Take an input n and print a number to n = done in for loop example 
Task2- Print all **even numbers** from `1` to `n`
import java.util.*;
public class practice1 {
    public static void main(String[] args) {
        Scanner sc = new Scanner(System.in);
        System.out.println("enter number");
        int num= sc.nextInt();
        for(int i=0;i<=num;i++){
         System.out.println(i);
         i++;
      }
    }
}

Task3- Find **sum of first n natural numbers**
import java.util.*;
public class practice1 {
  public static void main(String[] args) {
    Scanner sc = new Scanner(System.in);
    System.out.println("enter number");
    int num = sc.nextInt();
    int sum = 0;
    for (int i = 0; i <= num; i++) {
      sum = sum + i;
    }
    System.out.println(sum);
  }
}

Task4-  count digits in a number
import java.util.*;
public class practice1 {
  public static void main(String[] args) {
    Scanner sc = new Scanner(System.in);
    System.out.println("enter number");
    int num = sc.nextInt();
    int i = 0;
    while (num > 0) {
      i++;
      num = num / 10;
    }
    System.out.println(i);
  }
}
